SECOND REGULAR SESSION
SENATE BILL NO. 1031
103RD GENERA L ASSEMBLY
INTRODUCED BY SENATOR MOON.
5516S.01I KRISTINA MARTIN, Secretary
AN ACT
To amend chapter 1, RSMo, by adding thereto one new section relating to requirements for public
entities to achieve specific diversity, equity, or inclusion standards.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Missouri, as follows:
1 Section A. Chapter 1, RSMo, is amended by adding thereto
2 one new section, to be known as section 1.2030, to read as
3 follows:
1 1.2030. 1. No funds shall be expended by any state
2 department for intradepartmental programs, staffing, or
3 other initiatives associated with "diversity, equity, and
4 inclusion" or "diversity, inclusion, and belonging" or any
5 other initiative that promotes the preferential treatment of
6 any individual or group of individuals based on race, color,
7 religion, sex, gender, sexual orientation, ethnicity,
8 national origin, or ancestry and:
9 (1) The concept that disparities between groups are
10 solely the result of oppression;
11 (2) Collective guilt ideologies;
12 (3) Intersectional or divisive identity activism; or
13 (4) The limiting of freedom of conscience, thought, or
14 speech.
15 2. The provisions of subsection 1 of this section
16 shall not prohibit state departments from any of the
17 following:

SB 1031 2
18 (1) Following federal and state employment and
19 antidiscrimination laws; or
20 (2) Complying with the Americans with Disabilities
21 Act, 42 U.S.C. Section 12101, et seq.
22 3. No state department shall mandate, require, or
23 incentivize private sector employers to implement programs
24 or initiatives described in subsection 1 of this section as
25 a condition of awarding a state contract.
